<TITLE> HC orders govt to buy quake rescue gear </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 29 (bdnews24.com)The High Court on Wednesday ordered the government to form a committee within two months to buy equipment for post-earthquake rescue operations. The HC order said the committee should be headed by the home secretary and contain senior officials of the finance and disaster ministries. The director-general of the Fire Service and Civil Defence, two experts from public or private universities and two NGO representatives should also be part of the committee, said the HC order. The HC also said the finance ministry should pay for the equipment. Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh filed the petition in Dec 2008 with the bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossain and Quamrul Islam Siddiqui. 
